About
Whiskey Creek Country Club
Whiskey Creek Country Club
18 Holes
Par 60
3333 Yards
Slope 92
Rating 57.6
Bermuda Grass Greens
Whiskey Creek Country Club, built in 1974, has seasoned and well developed greens, fairways, tees and bunkers.  We welcome you to a unique world that combines a challenging executive golf course with unsurpassed social opportunities. Excellent golf and social membership are available. We are a friendly and affordable golf destination in beautiful South West Florida.
WCCC is challenging for low handicaps – we have over 32 bunkers protecting greens and many trees protecting fairways and greens.  You will definitely use every club in your bag. Our par 60 design also makes the course very enjoyable for high handicap golfers. High handicappers will no longer need to lumber through 500 yard par 5’s.  Our longest hole is 326 from the red tees and 336 from the blue tees which allow golfers of all levels the ability to compete and have fun at Whiskey Creek.
Being a par 60 has its privileges!  Most 18-hole rounds are completed well under the four hour time frame.

We've got what you need to hit the course!
The Pro Shop at WCCC offers both men’s and ladies golf shirts, jackets, hats & visors, golf gloves, sunglasses, golf balls as well as other golf novelty items. Gift Certificates purchased from the pro shop make a great gift.
